SIMPLE: self-government
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Self-government
<hw>Self`-gov"ern*ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The act of governing one's self, or the state of being governed by
one's self; self-control; self-command.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hence, government of a community, state, or nation
by the joint action of the mass of people constituting such a civil
body; also, the state of being so governed; democratic government;
democracy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It is to <qex>self-government</qex>, the great principle of
popular representation and administration, -- the system that lets in
all to participate in the councels that are to assign the good or evil
to all, -- that we may owe what we are and what we hope to be.</q>
<rj><qau>D. Webster.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Self-gratulation</ent>⟦br⟧
